{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KPHQhkjDKo5wXetyuA6Ecw","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: \"PRD-224.5\"\n3\ttitle: \"GitHub Action: flip review to done on PR merge\"\n4\tkind: task\n5\tstatus: ready\n6\tpriority: high\n7\teffort: s\n8\tcapability: simple\n9\tparent: \"[[PRD-224-harness-invariants-honest-state]]\"\n10\tdepends_on: []\n11\tblocks: []\n12\timpacts:\n13\t  - .github/workflows/prd-status-on-merge.yml\n14\tworkflow: null\n15\ttarget_version: null\n16\tcreated: 2026-04-08\n17\tupdated: 2026-04-08\n18\ttags:\n19\t  - harness\n20\t  - invariants\n21\t  - hygiene\n22\t---\n23\t\n24\t# GitHub Action: flip review to done on PR merge\n25\t\n26\t## Summary\n27\t\n28\tAdd a GitHub Action at `.github/workflows/prd-status-on-merge.yml` that fires when a PR targeting `main` is merged. If the PR's head branch matches `prd/PRD-*`, the action extracts the PRD ID, finds the corresponding PRD file, flips `status: review` to `status: done`, updates the `updated:` field, commits to main, and pushes.\n29\t\n30\tThis is a `[CI config]` — the structural fix for Mode 1 (status drift after merge). Once in place, the happy path is fully automated.\n31\t\n32\t## Requirements\n33\t\n34\t1. The action triggers on `pull_request` `closed` events on the `main` branch.\n35\t2. It only runs when the PR was actually merged (not just closed) AND the head branch starts with `prd/PRD-`.\n36\t3. It extracts the PRD ID from the branch name (e.g. `prd/PRD-216-foo` -> `PRD-216`).\n37\t4. It finds the PRD file matching `prds/${PRD_ID}-*.md`.\n38\t5. It flips `status: review` to `status: done` using sed (surgical, single-line replacement).\n39\t6. It updates the `updated:` field to today's date.\n40\t7. It commits with message `chore(prd): mark PRD-X done (auto-reconciled by merge action) [skip ci]` using a bot identity.\n41\t8. If no PRD file matches or the status is not `review`, the action exits 0 gracefully.\n42\t9. The action uses `[skip ci]` in the commit message to avoid triggering further CI runs.\n43\t\n44\t## Technical Approach\n45\t\n46\t### `.github/workflows/prd-status-on-merge.yml`\n47\t\n48\t```yaml\n49\tname: Reconcile PRD status on merge\n50\ton:\n51\t  pull_request:\n52\t    types: [closed]\n53\t    branches: [main]\n54\tjobs:\n55\t  flip-status:\n56\t    if: github.event.pull_request.merged == true && startsWith(github.event.pull_request.head.ref, 'prd/PRD-')\n57\t    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n58\t    permissions:\n59\t      contents: write\n60\t    steps:\n61\t      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n62\t        with:\n63\t          ref: main\n64\t          fetch-depth: 0\n65\t      - name: Flip status to done\n66\t        run: |\n67\t          BRANCH=\"${{ github.event.pull_request.head.ref }}\"\n68\t          PRD_ID=$(echo \"$BRANCH\" | sed -E 's|^prd/(PRD-[0-9.]+).*|\\1|')\n69\t          FILE=$(ls prds/${PRD_ID}-*.md 2>/dev/null || true)\n70\t          if [ -z \"$FILE\" ]; then\n71\t            echo \"No PRD file matching $PRD_ID -- skipping\"\n72\t            exit 0\n73\t          fi\n74\t          sed -i 's|^status: review$|status: done|' \"$FILE\"\n75\t          sed -i \"s|^updated: .*|updated: '$(date -u +%Y-%m-%d)'|\" \"$FILE\"\n76\t          if ! git diff --quiet \"$FILE\"; then\n77\t            git config user.name \"darkfactory-bot\"\n78\t            git config user.email \"darkfactory-bot@users.noreply.github.com\"\n79\t            git add \"$FILE\"\n80\t            git commit -m \"chore(prd): mark $PRD_ID done (auto-reconciled by merge action) [skip ci]\"\n81\t            git push\n82\t          fi\n83\t```\n84\t\n85\t## Acceptance Criteria\n86\t\n87\t- [ ] AC-1: `.github/workflows/prd-status-on-merge.yml` exists with the correct trigger and job config.\n88\t- [ ] AC-2: A test PR for a `prd/PRD-test-*` branch, when merged, triggers the action.\n89\t- [ ] AC-3: The action flips `status: review` to `status: done` in the correct PRD file.\n90\t- [ ] AC-4: The action updates the `updated:` field to the current date.\n91\t- [ ] AC-5: The action exits 0 gracefully when no matching PRD file exists.\n92\t- [ ] AC-6: The action exits 0 gracefully when the PRD status is not `review`.\n93\t- [ ] AC-7: The commit uses `[skip ci]` to avoid triggering further CI runs.\n94\t\n95\t## Open Questions\n96\t\n97\t- What about PRDs whose status field uses a different YAML quoting style than the sed pattern expects? The `update_frontmatter_field_at` function from PRD-214 is the robust answer, but the sed pattern is good enough for now since it matches the shape every other status mutation produces.\n98\t- What if the PRD file is missing on main? Action exits 0 with a log message.\n99\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7faefa45-9191-4c03-b927-60be620657a0","uuid":"28cb4c2d-0490-47f0-b524-3d17f765ae5f","timestamp":"2026-04-08T16:33:20.732Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/prds/PRD-224.5-gh-action-merge-status.md","content":"---\nid: \"PRD-224.5\"\ntitle: \"GitHub Action: flip review to done on PR merge\"\nkind: task\nstatus: ready\npriority: high\neffort: s\ncapability: simple\nparent: \"[[PRD-224-harness-invariants-honest-state]]\"\ndepends_on: []\nblocks: []\nimpacts:\n  - .github/workflows/prd-status-on-merge.yml\nworkflow: null\ntarget_version: null\ncreated: 2026-04-08\nupdated: 2026-04-08\ntags:\n  - harness\n  - invariants\n  - hygiene\n---\n\n# GitHub Action: flip review to done on PR merge\n\n## Summary\n\nAdd a GitHub Action at `.github/workflows/prd-status-on-merge.yml` that fires when a PR targeting `main` is merged. If the PR's head branch matches `prd/PRD-*`, the action extracts the PRD ID, finds the corresponding PRD file, flips `status: review` to `status: done`, updates the `updated:` field, commits to main, and pushes.\n\nThis is a `[CI config]` — the structural fix for Mode 1 (status drift after merge). Once in place, the happy path is fully automated.\n\n## Requirements\n\n1. The action triggers on `pull_request` `closed` events on the `main` branch.\n2. It only runs when the PR was actually merged (not just closed) AND the head branch starts with `prd/PRD-`.\n3. It extracts the PRD ID from the branch name (e.g. `prd/PRD-216-foo` -> `PRD-216`).\n4. It finds the PRD file matching `prds/${PRD_ID}-*.md`.\n5. It flips `status: review` to `status: done` using sed (surgical, single-line replacement).\n6. It updates the `updated:` field to today's date.\n7. It commits with message `chore(prd): mark PRD-X done (auto-reconciled by merge action) [skip ci]` using a bot identity.\n8. If no PRD file matches or the status is not `review`, the action exits 0 gracefully.\n9. The action uses `[skip ci]` in the commit message to avoid triggering further CI runs.\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### `.github/workflows/prd-status-on-merge.yml`\n\n```yaml\nname: Reconcile PRD status on merge\non:\n  pull_request:\n    types: [closed]\n    branches: [main]\njobs:\n  flip-status:\n    if: github.event.pull_request.merged == true && startsWith(github.event.pull_request.head.ref, 'prd/PRD-')\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      contents: write\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n        with:\n          ref: main\n          fetch-depth: 0\n      - name: Flip status to done\n        run: |\n          BRANCH=\"${{ github.event.pull_request.head.ref }}\"\n          PRD_ID=$(echo \"$BRANCH\" | sed -E 's|^prd/(PRD-[0-9.]+).*|\\1|')\n          FILE=$(ls prds/${PRD_ID}-*.md 2>/dev/null || true)\n          if [ -z \"$FILE\" ]; then\n            echo \"No PRD file matching $PRD_ID -- skipping\"\n            exit 0\n          fi\n          sed -i 's|^status: review$|status: done|' \"$FILE\"\n          sed -i \"s|^updated: .*|updated: '$(date -u +%Y-%m-%d)'|\" \"$FILE\"\n          if ! git diff --quiet \"$FILE\"; then\n            git config user.name \"darkfactory-bot\"\n            git config user.email \"darkfactory-bot@users.noreply.github.com\"\n            git add \"$FILE\"\n            git commit -m \"chore(prd): mark $PRD_ID done (auto-reconciled by merge action) [skip ci]\"\n            git push\n          fi\n```\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: `.github/workflows/prd-status-on-merge.yml` exists with the correct trigger and job config.\n- [ ] AC-2: A test PR for a `prd/PRD-test-*` branch, when merged, triggers the action.\n- [ ] AC-3: The action flips `status: review` to `status: done` in the correct PRD file.\n- [ ] AC-4: The action updates the `updated:` field to the current date.\n- [ ] AC-5: The action exits 0 gracefully when no matching PRD file exists.\n- [ ] AC-6: The action exits 0 gracefully when the PRD status is not `review`.\n- [ ] AC-7: The commit uses `[skip ci]` to avoid triggering further CI runs.\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- What about PRDs whose status field uses a different YAML quoting style than the sed pattern expects? The `update_frontmatter_field_at` function from PRD-214 is the robust answer, but the sed pattern is good enough for now since it matches the shape every other status mutation produces.\n- What if the PRD file is missing on main? Action exits 0 with a log message.\n","numLines":99,"startLine":1,"totalLines":99}}}
